author: yaxir137
content:
I have a question about network **re-configuration**
currently, my test network takes 8 hours to activate a new validator ( so after deposit i have to wait around 8 hours, before the validator can start earning rewards)
i know, i can modify the config.yaml file to speed up the block production, epochs etc
but I wonder if that will require me to Start a new network ( as i need to generate another genesis.ssz for that configuration)
i don't want to start a new network, since we have some important NFTs and some other data (work done by students) on the existing testnet
therefore, my question being:
**How can i modify the network parameters / network configuration for a testnet that is currently running**
we have 3 nodes, on 3 different machines
i have total control over all of them

author: yaxir137
content: any help is massively appreciated!

author: mariusvanderwijden
content: Pretty hard to do on an existing nw, your best bet is to do a hardfork of your network or maybe do a regenesis
